'''''American Roots Music''''' is a 2001 multi-part [[documentary film]] that explores the historical roots of American Roots music through footage and performances by the creators of the movement: Folk, Country, Blues, Gospel, Bluegrass, and many others.

This [[Public Broadcasting Service|PBS]] film series is available as an 'in-class' teaching tool.[http://www.pbs.org/americanrootsmusic/pbs_arm_into_the_classroom.html]

Notable musicians that appear in this documentary are:
*[[Kris Kristofferson]] (as narrator) 
*[[Bonnie Raitt]]
*[[Robbie Robertson]]
*[[Bob Dylan]]
*[[Eddie Vedder]]
*[[Mike Seeger]]
*[[Ricky Skaggs]]
*[[Marty Stuart]]
*[[Rufus Thomas]]
*[[Doc Watson]]
*[[James Cotton]]
*[[Bela Fleck]]
*[[Douglas B. Green]]
*[[Arlo Guthrie]] 
*[[Flaco Jim<U+00E9>nez]]
*[[B.B. King]]
*[[Bruce Springsteen]]
*[[Steven Van Zandt]]
*[[Robert Mirabal]]
*[[Keb' Mo']]
*[[Willie Nelson]]
*[[Sam Phillips]]
*[[Bernice Johnson Reagon]]
*[[Keith Richards]]
*[[Earl Scruggs]]
*[[Ralph Stanley]]

